LINQ Bound Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph xml:space="preserve">Language integrated query (LINQ) is a Microsoft .NET Framework component that adds native data querying capabilities to .NET languages using syntax reminiscent of SQL. A heatmap control can bind data from a LINQ data source and populate the data from its object. The following sample  demonstrates this feature.</Paragraph><Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
<Image Source="images/LINQ Bound Demo.png" Height="520" Width="750" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>A heatmap control can bind data from a LINQ data source and populate the data from its object.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features</Paragraph>


<List Margin="25,0,0,0">


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The slider called <Bold>"Select Median Weight"</Bold> will change the interior of a heatmap item. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combobox <Bold>"Top Level LayOut"</Bold> will change the top level layout. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combobox <Bold>"Inner Level LayOut"</Bold> selects the inner level layout. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>


<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The button <Bold>"Toggle Weight Value Path"</Bold> will toggle a heatmap item's weight.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>
